// Page HelloPage Text :
"P3252439049" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Above the Law</color></span></scale></font><br><br><span align=center><color orange><i>Vigilante Morality Mission</i></color></span><br><br>You overhear some people talking about Blast Furnace being arrested. You've heard that he's been riding on the edge of the law lately in his attempts to keep the streets clean. Looking into it, you find a report filed by the PPD...<br><br><scale 1.1><font face=computer><color BurlyWood>You discover from the PPD report that Blast Furnace was part of an attack on a hidden Malta cell within Paragon City. Things were looking bad in the fight and it appeared that Malta was going to launch a series of their Zeus Titans into the heart of Kings Row. Blast Furnace set off a number of explosive charges in the facility, causing the entire place to explode. Kings Row was saved; However, Blast Furnace killed a large number of PPD. Because of this, he has been sentenced to the Zig, but may receive an early probation for good behavior.</color></font></scale><br><br>Blast Furnace <i>saves</i> Kings Row and his reward is being sent to prison? This is outrageous! Yes, some members of the PPD were killed by his hand, but does that make him a murderer like all the other inmates in the Zig? Absolutely not! Someone needs to go to the Zig and get Blast Furnace out. Paragon City needs more people like him in the streets who are willing to get their hands dirty to keep this city safe.<br><br><color orange>WARNING: This is a Morality Mission. Completing this mission will change your alignment to Vigilante. This means that the people of Paragon City will no longer see you as a Hero. Becoming a Vigilante means you will gain the ability to travel to the Rogue Isles, once you've completed this mission.</color>"
// Answer Text :
"P3468881128" "Get Blast Furnace out of the Zig!"
